1. Write your complete plan to `.ralph/work-plan.txt`
2. **CRITICAL: The plan MUST start with a markdown checklist.** The very first line must be exactly:
   ```
   ## Implementation Checklist
   ```
   Followed by checklist items like `- [ ] 1. Step description`. All checklist items MUST be unchecked (`- [ ]`) in the PLAN output. Do NOT include any preamble, session logs, or prompt text before the checklist header.
   **The second-to-last checklist item MUST always be `- [ ] N. Update `.ralph/exploration.md` if any implementation changed documented files, patterns, or schema`** — this keeps exploration notes accurate for future specs.
   **The last checklist item MUST always be `- [ ] N. All acceptance criteria pass — run `ralph validate work` and confirm PASS`** — this is the final gate before the spec is considered complete. Note: the WORK agent executes this checklist, so validation must use `ralph validate work` (not `ralph validate plan`).
